---
import ReportLayout from '@/components/ReportLayout.astro';
---

<ReportLayout title="Getting Started">

  <section class="gs-intro">
    <p class="gs-eyebrow">Setup Guide</p>
    <h1 class="gs-h1">Getting started</h1>
    <p class="gs-summary">
      The UX Intelligence agents run inside <strong>Claude Code</strong> — available as a desktop
      app that connects Claude directly to a local copy of this repository on your machine.
      You'll need a GitHub account with access to the repo, the repo cloned locally, the Claude
      Code desktop app installed, two plugins (a Chrome extension and a GitHub connector), and
      the agent skills activated. This guide walks you through each step.
    </p>
    <div class="gs-notice">
      <strong>Why Claude Code, not Claude.ai?</strong>
      Claude.ai can chat and analyse pages, but it can't write files to this repository or push
      commits — so reports won't be saved and screenshots won't appear on the site. Claude Code
      runs in the context of the repo on your machine, which is what gives it permission to
      create report files, commit screenshots, and push everything live.
    </div>
    <p class="gs-terminal-note">
      <strong>Prefer the terminal?</strong> If you're already comfortable with git and npm,
      <code>npm install -g @anthropic-ai/claude-code</code> then <code>claude</code> from
      inside the repo is all you need. The rest of this guide focuses on the desktop app.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 1: GitHub account ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">1</span>
      Create a GitHub account
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      If you don't already have one, sign up for a free GitHub account. You'll need this to
      request access to the private repository.
    </p>
    <a href="https://github.com/signup" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-external-link">
      <span class="gs-external-icon">↗</span>
      github.com/signup — create a free account
    </a>
    <p class="gs-body gs-body--note">
      Use your THG work email address so it's easy for the repo admin to verify who you are
      when granting access.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 2: Repo access ───────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">2</span>
      Request access to the repository
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      The repository is private. Once you have a GitHub account, contact Richard Gill and
      share your GitHub username — he'll add you as a collaborator and GitHub will send you
      an email invite. Accept the invite to gain write access.
    </p>
    <div class="gs-repo-card">
      <div class="gs-repo-header">
        <span class="gs-repo-icon">◈</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-repo-org">THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds</p>
          <p class="gs-repo-name">ux-prototyping</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p class="gs-repo-desc">
        The UX Intelligence site and all agent-generated reports. Private — requires an invite.
      </p>
      <a href="https://github.com/THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-repo-link">
        View on GitHub →
      </a>
    </div>
    <p class="gs-body gs-body--note">
      Write access is required — not just read access. This is what allows Claude Code to commit
      new report files and push them to the site on your behalf.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 3: Clone the repo ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">3</span>
      Clone the repository to your machine
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      The agents need the repo to exist as a local folder on your machine — they write files
      directly into it. The easiest way to clone it is with <strong>GitHub Desktop</strong>,
      a free app that handles authentication and gives you a simple UI for committing and
      pushing changes.
    </p>

    <div class="gs-substeps">

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">3a</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Download GitHub Desktop</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">Install GitHub Desktop and sign in with your GitHub account.</p>
          <a href="https://desktop.github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-external-link">
            <span class="gs-external-icon">↗</span>
            desktop.github.com
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">3b</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Clone the repository</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">
            In GitHub Desktop: <strong>File → Clone Repository</strong>, then search for
            <code>THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping</code>. Choose a local path you'll
            remember — for example <code>~/Documents/GitHub/ux-prototyping</code>. Click
            <strong>Clone</strong>.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">3c</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Note the local path</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">
            In GitHub Desktop, go to <strong>Repository → Show in Finder</strong> (Mac) or
            <strong>Show in Explorer</strong> (Windows). Note the full folder path — you'll
            need to point Claude Code at this folder in step 5.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 4: Install Claude Code desktop app ───────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">4</span>
      Install the Claude Code desktop app
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Claude Code is built into the Claude desktop app. Download it from Anthropic and sign in
      with your Anthropic account. If you don't have one, a Claude Pro plan ($20/month) is
      sufficient for running the agents.
    </p>
    <a href="https://claude.ai/download" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-external-link">
      <span class="gs-external-icon">↗</span>
      claude.ai/download — download the desktop app
    </a>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Once installed, open the app and sign in. You'll land in a standard Claude chat interface —
      Claude Code is accessed via the project/folder selector, which you'll set up in the next step.
    </p>
    <div class="gs-tip">
      <strong>Not sure if you have an Anthropic account?</strong>
      If you use Claude.ai in a browser already, you have an account — use the same credentials
      to log in to the desktop app.
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 5: Open the repo ─────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">5</span>
      Open the repository in Claude Code
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      This is the step that connects Claude Code to the local repo on your machine — without
      this, the agents can't write report files or commit screenshots.
    </p>

    <div class="gs-substeps">

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">5a</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Open a new project</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">
            In the Claude desktop app, look for <strong>Claude Code</strong> or the
            <strong>terminal/project icon</strong> — it's usually in the left sidebar or
            accessible via the menu. Click it to open the Claude Code panel.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">5b</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Select the repo folder</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">
            Claude Code will prompt you to select a project folder. Navigate to the
            <code>ux-prototyping</code> folder you cloned in step 3 and select it. Claude
            Code will start in the context of that folder — it now has access to all the
            repo files and can write new ones.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">5c</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Confirm it's working</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">
            Type <code>/</code> in the Claude Code prompt. You should see a list of available
            slash commands. If you can see the list, the session is running correctly inside
            the repo.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 6: Plugins ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">6</span>
      Install required plugins
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Two plugins are needed for the agents to work properly: a Chrome browser extension so
      Claude can navigate to pages and take screenshots, and a GitHub connector so Claude can
      push commits to the repo. Both are configured in Claude Code's settings.
    </p>

    <!-- Chrome extension -->
    <div class="gs-plugin-card">
      <div class="gs-plugin-header">
        <span class="gs-plugin-badge gs-plugin-badge--chrome">Chrome</span>
        <h3 class="gs-plugin-name">Claude in Chrome extension</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="gs-plugin-desc">
        This extension connects Claude Code to your Chrome browser. Without it, the UX Review
        and Competitor Analysis agents can't open URLs, scroll pages, or take screenshots —
        which are the core of what those agents do.
      </p>
      <div class="gs-plugin-steps">
        <p class="gs-plugin-step"><span class="gs-plugin-step-num">1</span> Install the extension from the Chrome Web Store:</p>
        <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/claude/pnaoflhkifljdmpmollaobhbknaeeafh" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-external-link gs-external-link--sm">
          <span class="gs-external-icon">↗</span>
          Claude extension — Chrome Web Store
        </a>
        <p class="gs-plugin-step"><span class="gs-plugin-step-num">2</span> Once installed, open a Chrome tab and click the extension icon — you'll be prompted to connect it to your Claude account. Sign in with the same account you use in the desktop app.</p>
        <p class="gs-plugin-step"><span class="gs-plugin-step-num">3</span> In Claude Code, the extension will appear automatically as an available tool. You can confirm it's connected by typing <code>/</code> and looking for Chrome-related tools in the list.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- GitHub MCP -->
    <div class="gs-plugin-card">
      <div class="gs-plugin-header">
        <span class="gs-plugin-badge gs-plugin-badge--github">GitHub</span>
        <h3 class="gs-plugin-name">GitHub MCP connector</h3>
      </div>
      <p class="gs-plugin-desc">
        This connector gives Claude Code deeper GitHub integration — it can read repository
        structure, check commit history, and authenticate pushes. Without it, Claude can still
        run git commands locally but won't have full GitHub context.
      </p>
      <div class="gs-plugin-steps">
        <p class="gs-plugin-step"><span class="gs-plugin-step-num">1</span> In the Claude desktop app, go to <strong>Settings → Extensions</strong> (or <strong>Integrations</strong> depending on your version) and search for <strong>GitHub</strong>.</p>
        <p class="gs-plugin-step"><span class="gs-plugin-step-num">2</span> Click <strong>Connect</strong> and authorise Claude to access your GitHub account. This will open a GitHub OAuth page — approve the access for the <code>THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds</code> organisation.</p>
        <p class="gs-plugin-step"><span class="gs-plugin-step-num">3</span> Once connected, GitHub will appear as an available tool in Claude Code sessions. You only need to do this once — it persists across sessions.</p>
      </div>
      <p class="gs-body gs-body--note" style="margin-top: 12px; margin-bottom: 0;">
        If you can't see the GitHub integration in Settings, it may not be available on your
        Claude plan. Basic git operations (commit, push, pull) still work without it — the
        agents use your local git credentials directly. GitHub Desktop handles authentication
        automatically so pushes should work even without the MCP connector.
      </p>
    </div>

  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 7: Install skills ────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">7</span>
      Install the agent skills
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      The UX Intelligence agents are packaged as <em>skills</em> — reusable, named workflows
      that Claude runs when you type a slash command. Skills are stored in a folder on your
      machine, not inside the repo itself. You need to copy the skill files from the repo into
      that folder once, and Claude Code will pick them up automatically from then on.
    </p>

    <div class="gs-substeps">

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">7a</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Paste this prompt into Claude Code</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">
            With the repo open in Claude Code, copy and paste the prompt below and press
            Enter. Claude will find the right folder, copy the skills in, and confirm what
            it installed.
          </p>
          <div class="gs-copyblock">
            <pre class="gs-code gs-code--wrap" id="install-prompt">Please install the UX Intelligence agent skills from this repo into my Claude skills folder. The skills are in `src/skills/user/` — find my Claude skills directory at `~/Library/Application Support/Claude/local-agent-mode-sessions/skills-plugin/` and copy each skill folder from the repo into it. If you find multiple skills subfolders, copy into all of them. Confirm which skills were installed and where.</pre>
            <button class="gs-copy-btn" onclick="
              navigator.clipboard.writeText(document.getElementById('install-prompt').innerText);
              this.textContent = 'Copied!';
              setTimeout(() => this.textContent = 'Copy', 2000);
            ">Copy</button>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">7b</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Restart Claude Desktop</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">
            Quit the Claude desktop app completely and reopen it. Skills are loaded at
            startup — a restart is required for the new ones to appear.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="gs-substep">
        <span class="gs-substep-label">7c</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-substep-title">Confirm all four agents are available</p>
          <p class="gs-substep-body">
            With the repo open in Claude Code, type <code>/</code> to open the slash command
            picker. You should see all four agent commands in the list:
          </p>
          <div class="gs-skill-list">
            <div class="gs-skill-row">
              <code class="gs-skill-cmd">/myprotein-ux-review</code>
              <span class="gs-skill-label">UX Review agent</span>
            </div>
            <div class="gs-skill-row">
              <code class="gs-skill-cmd">/competitor-analysis</code>
              <span class="gs-skill-label">Competitor Analysis agent</span>
            </div>
            <div class="gs-skill-row">
              <code class="gs-skill-cmd">/design-qa</code>
              <span class="gs-skill-label">Design QA agent</span>
            </div>
            <div class="gs-skill-row">
              <code class="gs-skill-cmd">/myprotein-prep-agent</code>
              <span class="gs-skill-label">Project Prep agent</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <p class="gs-substep-body" style="margin-top: 12px;">
            If any are missing, see the troubleshooting section below.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Step 8: First report ───────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">
      <span class="gs-step-badge">8</span>
      Run your first report
    </h2>
    <p class="gs-body">
      You're ready. Trigger the UX Review agent with any Myprotein URL:
    </p>
    <pre class="gs-code">/myprotein-ux-review https://www.myprotein.com/sports-nutrition/impact-whey-protein/10530943.html</pre>
    <p class="gs-body">
      Claude Code will navigate to the page in Chrome, take screenshots, analyse the UX, write
      the report file, and commit and push it to GitHub — all automatically. When it's done,
      it will give you a direct link to the live report. You don't need to touch GitHub Desktop.
    </p>

    <p class="gs-body" style="margin-top: 8px;">
      See the <a href="/agents/ux-review" class="gs-inline-link">agent guides</a> for a
      detailed walkthrough of each agent, what to expect at every step, and how to handle
      common issues.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Troubleshooting ────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">Common setup issues</h2>
    <ul class="gs-tips-list">
      <li>
        <strong>Claude Code can't find the repo folder.</strong>
        Make sure you selected the root <code>ux-prototyping</code> folder — not a subfolder
        like <code>src/</code> or <code>src/pages/</code>. The repo root is the folder that
        contains <code>package.json</code> and <code>src/</code>. If you're not sure, use
        GitHub Desktop's <strong>Show in Finder / Explorer</strong> to open the exact folder,
        then drag that folder into Claude Code's project selector.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Slash commands show up but the agents don't run — just errors.</strong>
        The most common cause is the Chrome extension not being connected. Open Chrome, click
        the Claude extension icon, and make sure it shows as connected (not "disconnected" or
        "sign in required"). The UX Review and Competitor Analysis agents both need Chrome open
        and connected before they'll work.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>GitHub Desktop push fails — "permission denied" or "authentication failed".</strong>
        This usually means you accepted the repo invite but GitHub Desktop hasn't refreshed your
        permissions. In GitHub Desktop, go to <strong>GitHub Desktop → Preferences → Accounts</strong>,
        sign out, and sign back in. Then try the push again.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>The skills aren't appearing after following step 7.</strong>
        First, make sure you fully quit and restarted Claude Desktop after running the install
        prompt — skills are only loaded at startup. If they're still missing, run the install
        prompt again and check that Claude confirms the files were copied. If Claude says it
        can't find the skills folder, it may not have been created yet — make sure you've
        opened Claude Desktop and used Claude Code at least once before running the prompt.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong>Can I use Claude.ai in a browser tab instead of the desktop app?</strong>
        For exploring and analysing, yes. But Claude.ai can't write to this repo, commit
        screenshots, or push to the site. For anything that produces a saved report, use the
        Claude Code desktop app with the repo folder open.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ── Quick links ────────────────────────────────────────── -->
  <section class="gs-section">
    <h2 class="gs-section-heading">Quick links</h2>
    <div class="gs-links-grid">
      <a href="https://github.com/THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">◈</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">GitHub repository</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">THG-AltitudeSiteBuilds/ux-prototyping</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="https://claude.ai/download" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">⌘</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">Claude desktop app</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">Download for Mac or Windows</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="https://desktop.github.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">⎇</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">GitHub Desktop</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">Clone, commit, and push without the terminal</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/claude/pnaoflhkifljdmpmollaobhbknaeeafh" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">⬡</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">Claude Chrome extension</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">Required for screenshot and page navigation</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="/agents/ux-review" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">↗</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">Agent guides</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">Step-by-step for each agent type</p>
        </div>
      </a>
      <a href="https://docs.anthropic.com/en/docs/claude-code/getting-started" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="gs-link-card">
        <span class="gs-link-icon">⬚</span>
        <div>
          <p class="gs-link-title">Claude Code docs</p>
          <p class="gs-link-sub">Official Anthropic documentation</p>
        </div>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

</ReportLayout>

<style>
  .gs-intro {
    margin-bottom: 52px;
  }
  .gs-eyebrow {
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    color: var(--color-primary);
    opacity: 0.5;
    margin-bottom: 10px;
  }
  .gs-h1 {
    font-size: clamp(26px, 4vw, 38px);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 16px;
    line-height: 1.15;
  }
  .gs-summary {
    font-size: 15px;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 20px;
  }
  .gs-notice {
    background: #FFF8E1;
    border: 1px solid rgba(230, 81, 0, 0.2);
    border-left: 4px solid #E65100;
    border-radius: 0 8px 8px 0;
    padding: 14px 18px;
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    max-width: 680px;
    margin-bottom: 14px;
  }
  .gs-notice strong {
    display: block;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #BF360C;
    margin-bottom: 4px;
  }
  .gs-terminal-note {
    font-size: 13px;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    opacity: 0.6;
    max-width: 680px;
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 10px 14px;
  }
  .gs-terminal-note strong { font-weight: 700; opacity: 1; color: var(--color-text-heading); }

  /* ── Sections ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .gs-section {
    margin-bottom: 52px;
  }
  .gs-section-heading {
    font-size: 20px;
    font-weight: 800;
    color: var(--color-text-heading);
    margin-bottom: 18px;
    padding-bottom: 12px;
    border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.08);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 14px;
  }
  .gs-step-badge {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    width: 32px;
    height: 32px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-mint);
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 800;
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
  }

  .gs-body {
    font-size: 14px;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--color-text-body);
    margin-bottom: 14px;
    max-width: 680px;
  }
  .gs-body--note {
    background: var(--color-bg-muted);
    border-left: 3px solid var(--color-mint);
    padding: 10px 14px;
    border-radius: 0 6px 6px 0;
    margin-top: 4px;
  }

  .gs-inline-link {
    color: var(--color-primary);
    font-weight: 600;
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }
  .gs-inline-link:hover { opacity: 0.75; }

  /* ── Substeps ───────────────────────────────────────────── */
  .gs-substeps {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 680px;
    border: var(--card-border);
    border-radius: var(--radius-card);
    overflow: hidden;
    background: var(--color-bg-card);
  }
  .gs-substep {
    display: flex;
    gap: 16px;
    align-items: flex-start;
    padding: 18px 20px;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0,57,66,0.07);
  }
  .gs-substep:last-child { border-bottom: none; }
  .gs-substep-label {
    flex-shrink: 0;
    min-width: 28px;
    height: 28px;
